<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11832] Spark shell does not work from sbt with scala 2.11</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11832</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using Scala 2.11, running the spark shell task from within sbt fails, however running it from a distribution works.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Stepstoreproduce&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Steps to reproduce&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;change scala version &lt;tt&gt;dev/change-scala-version.sh 2.11&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;start sbt &lt;tt&gt;build/sbt -Dscala-2.11&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;run shell task &lt;tt&gt;sparkShell&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Stacktrace&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Stacktrace&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Failed to initialize compiler: object scala in compiler mirror not found.
** Note that as of 2.8 scala does not assume use of the java classpath.
** For the old behavior pass -usejavacp to scala, or &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; using a Settings
** object programmatically, settings.usejavacp.value = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;.
Exception in thread &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;main&quot;&lt;/span&gt; java.lang.NullPointerException
